        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I am sure I have seen this mentioned but can't find it now. In the modules resource the default module can't have a it's own bootstrap.\n\nI would of thought this should be changed to allow any module to be used as a default, which may in turn have it's own bootstrap file.\n\nIs the idea that the application bootstrap should extend your default modules bootstrap?"
